ically cover a lot of leaks or rumors because they can be, and often are, completely wrong or blown out of proportion. You never know when something\u0026#39;s actually true until it\u0026#39;s official. If this one is true, however, it might end up changing your summer purchase plans if you were waiting for this year\u0026#39;s new Samsung foldables.\u003c/p\u003e\n\t\t\t\n\n                    \n\n\n                \n                \n                \n                \n\n                \n                \n                \n                \t\n\n\n                \n\n                \n                \n                \n            \u003c/div\u003e\n                \n        \n        \n        \n            \u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eBeyond the immediate credit, Samsung is also tossing in triple Samsung reward points on your pre-order purchase. If you\u0026#39;re already in the Samsung ecosystem, you know how quickly those points can add up for future discounts and exclusive offers. It\u0026#39;s a nice little incentive to keep you coming back. And if that wasn\u0026#39;t enough, by reserving your spot, you\u0026#39;re automatically entered into a sweepstakes with a grand prize of $5,000.\u003c/p\u003e    \u003cp\u003eNow, about the phones themselves. Leaks and rumors suggest Samsung is pushing the envelope a bit more this year. The Galaxy Z Fold 7 is rumored to be noticeably thinner and lighter than its predecessors, addressing one of the biggest complaints about past Fold models. There have also been reports of a larger main display and potentially a switch back to a punch-hole camera on both the inner and outer screens for improved image quality, moving away from the less-than-stellar under-display camera technology.\u003c/p\u003e        \n\u003cp\u003eAs for the Galaxy Z Flip 7, expect a larger cover display, bringing it more in line with the Motorola Razr line. This should make the outer screen far more useful for quick glances and interactions \u003ca 